{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848530853,"sessionID":"ses_2872e4d67ffes0XxVhFdR950hT","part":{"id":"prt_d78d22371001aEBKeRXLEe7P3s","messageID":"msg_d78d204ce001OchCl8UlI3rwbh","sessionID":"ses_2872e4d67ffes0XxVhFdR950hT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a3a79812196d485ba1b1ff3198f7de38","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md","limit":50,"offset":575},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n575: 9. **Documentation** - Complete documentation for GC functionality\n576: 10. **RBAC Updates** - Permissions for GC operations\n577: \n578: ### Success Criteria\n579: - All unit tests pass with >80% code coverage\n580: - All integration tests pass\n581: - GC scheduler runs periodically\n582: - Expired sandboxes are identified and deleted\n583: - Idle sandboxes are identified and deleted\n584: - Orphaned sandboxes are identified and deleted\n585: - Resources are properly cleaned up (K8s + Store)\n586: - DryRun mode works correctly\n587: - Metrics are emitted correctly\n588: - Events are recorded correctly\n589: - Logs are structured and informative\n590: - RBAC permissions are correct\n591: - Code passes static analysis and linting\n592: - Documentation is complete and accurate\n593: \n594: ### Dependencies\n595: - Go 1.24+\n596: - Kubernetes cluster (for testing)\n597: - Redis/Valkey (for session store)\n598: - agent-sandbox CRD (agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1)\n599: - SandboxClaim CRD (extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1)\n600: - AR-006 (Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management) - for basic GC functionality\n601: - k8s.io/client-go v0.34.1\n602: - k8s.io/api v0.34.1\n603: - k8s.io/apimachinery v0.34.1\n604: - go-redis/v9 or valkey-go (Redis client)\n605: - prometheus/client_golang (metrics)\n606: - sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime (event recorder)\n607: \n608: ### Blocked By\n609: - None (design stage ST-3 completed)\n610: \n611: ### Blocks\n612: - None (this is an enhancement to AR-006, can proceed independently)\n613: \n614: ### Notes\n615: - AR-008 enhances the basic GC functionality from AR-006 with:\n616:   - More sophisticated scheduling\n617:   - Configurable policies\n618:   - Metrics and observability\n619:   - Event recording\n620:   - Better configuration options\n621: - GC runs independently in background, can be started/stopped with server\n622: - DryRun mode allows testing without actual deletions\n623: - Namespace and label filtering allows selective GC\n624: - Idempotency ensures safe retries and concurrent operations\n\n(Showing lines 575-624 of 626. Use offset=625 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"9. **Documentation** - Complete documentation for GC functionality\n10. **RBAC Updates** - Permissions for GC operations\n\n### Success Criteria\n- All unit tests pass with >80% code coverage\n- All integration tests pass\n- GC scheduler runs periodically\n- Expired sandboxes are identified and deleted\n- Idle sandboxes are identified and deleted\n- Orphaned sandboxes are identified and deleted\n- Resources are properly cleaned up (K8s + Store)\n- DryRun mode works correctly\n- Metrics are emitted correctly\n- Events are recorded correctly\n- Logs are structured and informative\n- RBAC permissions are correct\n- Code passes static analysis and linting\n- Documentation is complete and accurate\n\n### Dependencies","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775848530832,"end":1775848530851}}}}
